<HTMLInputElementPlaceholder>
<summary>
The <strong><c>placeholder</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLInputElement"/> interface represents a hint to the user of what can be entered in the control. It reflects the {{htmlelement("input")}} element's <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#placeholder"><c>placeholder</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input">input</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.Value"/><br/>-{{cssxref(&amp;quot;::placeholder&amp;quot;)}} pseudo-element<br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:placeholder-shown">:placeholder-shown</see> pseudo-class<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLInputElement/placeholder"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
</HTMLInputElementPlaceholder>
